BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, April 22 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
steering council of the ruling Mongolian People's Revolutionary 
Party [MPRP] has called upon all the participants of political 
hunger strike to cease their action. As was said in the appeal, 
the following reasons should be taken into consideration for 
ceasing the hunger strikes as the decisions by the council for 
ensuring the national security, that of the Mongolian parliament 
as well as out of respect of national traditions and Mongolian 
statehood. 

